    "When this option is used, the context image is a thumbnail of the WSI, with background and areas outside ROIs removed to prevent pen marks and other artifacts from interfering with stain deconvolution.",
    "Contextual normalization is not recommended when artifact removal is suboptimal or ROIs are unavailable.",
    "Training weakly-supervised, tile-based modelsSlideflow includes several tools for training deep learning classification, regression, and time-to-event models for WSIs.",
    "Weakly-supervised, tile-based models use a deep learning image classifier to generate predictions for all tiles in a slide, and the final slide-level prediction is calculated by averaging tile predictions (Fig. 3).",
    "Although this method may be limited with highly heterogeneous tumors or when salient morphological features are sparse, it has proven to be an effective approach for a variety of biological applications [6,[37][38][39]."
